  <h3>Malaspina Glacier Fieldwork and Research</h3>
  <p>
    The Malaspina Glacier is an enourmus piedmont glacier in the southeastern
    corner of the park. A collaborative NPS/NSF research project was initiated
    this summer when a team of NPS, University of Alaska Fairbanks, and
    University of Arizona spent two weeks surveying the forelands and proglacial
    lakes. The goal is to quantify the timing and likelihood of catastrophic
    retreat in the event that Malaspina becomes a tidewater glacier.
  </p>
